However, this model fixes the choice of B based on the highest price from the delivery sites at a given point in the future, which means it does not fully capture the optionality available in real-world operations. Specifically, it neglects the flexibility to switch between delivery points dynamically, depending on price changes at different sites over time. This fixed choice limits the valuation since it doesnâ€™t reflect the strategic flexibility the operator has to choose the optimal delivery site on an ongoing basis.

New Model: Full Optionality Valuation
The new model proposes a full optionality valuation, where both the receiving and delivery sites are optimized, and switching optionality is incorporated. The updated payoff formula is still:

